How to modify site name

To modify site-name edit FASTN/ws.ftd file which is added inside your fastn project root FASTN folder.

Edit FASTN/ws.ftd line optional string site-name: Midnight.

E.g.
null
optional string site-name: ACME.com

optional string site-name: ACME.com
Lang:
info

If you dont want to show site-name and keep it blank, and show only logo. Then first add logo, to add logo follow How to enable site logo

Once you have finished adding logo, then just remove Midnight from line optional string site-name: Midnight replace this with optional string site-name:

How to enable site logo

To enable site-logo edit FASTN/ws.ftd file which is added inside your fastn project root FASTN folder.

To add site-logo add logo dark and light image inside assets folder. assets folder is already added inside your fastn project root folder.

After adding logo image inside assets folder, update below lines from FASTN/ws.ftd file.

Change below line:
null
-- ftd.image-src fastn-logo: https://fastn.com/-/fastn.com/images/fastn.svg

-- ftd.image-src fastn-logo: https://fastn.com/-/fastn.com/images/fastn.svg
Lang:
ftd
with:
null
-- ftd.image-src fastn-logo: $assets.files.assets.ipsum-logo.svg

-- ftd.image-src fastn-logo: $assets.files.assets.ipsum-logo.svg
Lang:
ftd

In above code snippet we have used ipsum-logo.svg file which is already added as dummy logo inside your fastn project folder.

Now edit FASTN/ws.ftd line optional ftd.image-src site-logo:.

E.g.
null
optional ftd.image-src site-logo: $fastn-logo

optional ftd.image-src site-logo: $fastn-logo
Lang:
ftd
Now deploy your fastn site or run your local server. ipsum-logo will be seen before site-name

How to modify site-logo height and width

We have added option for you to modify height or width of your site logo. For this we have added logo-width and logo-height integer type properties inside FASTN/ws.ftd file.

Since logo-width and logo-height are of integer type, just update its value in numbers only.

E.g.

Change below lines:
null
integer logo-width: $common.logo-width
integer logo-height: $common.logo-height

integer logo-width: $common.logo-width
integer logo-height: $common.logo-height
Lang:
info
with(if you only wish to change width):
null
integer logo-width: 120
integer logo-height: $common.logo-height

integer logo-width: 120
integer logo-height: $common.logo-height
Lang:
info
with(if you only wish to change height):
null
integer logo-width: $common.logo-width
integer logo-height: 48

integer logo-width: $common.logo-width
integer logo-height: 48
Lang:
info
with(if you only wish to change height and width):
null
integer logo-width: 120
integer logo-height: 48

integer logo-width: 120
integer logo-height: 48
Lang:
info

How to update Navbar links

To update navbar links, update FASTN.ftd -- fastn.sitemap: links. Edit FASTN.ftd file which is inside your fastn project root folder.

If you would like to change Services link name with Our Services then follow below code snippet:
null
-- fastn.sitemap:

# Home: index.html
# Our Services: /#services
# About: /#about
# Testimonials: /#testimonials
# Clients: /#clients
# FAQs: /#faqs

-- fastn.sitemap:

# Home: index.html
# Our Services: /#services
# About: /#about
# Testimonials: /#testimonials
# Clients: /#clients
# FAQs: /#faqs
Lang:
info
